ry ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "US sports") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "MLS") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "San Jose Earthquakes") (pubDate nil "Wed, 17 Apr 2013 13:50:14 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/blog/2013/apr/17/george-john-fc-dallas-bottle-head") (dc:creator nil "Graham Parker") (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-17T15:27:38Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407328147") (media:keywords nil "MLS, Sport, US sports, Football, FC Dallas, San Jose Earthquakes") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366212340144/a3cf8c3c-27ce-4555-95e6-ee8afa0be4b5-140x84.jpeg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Andrew Dieb/Icon SMI/Icon SMI/Photoshot") (media:description nil "After scoring the winning goal, FC Dallas defender George John is hit in the head with a beer bottle during the game between LA Galaxy and FC Dallas at FC Dallas Stadium. Photograph: Andrew Dieb/Icon SMI/Photoshot")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/4/17/1366212339047/a3cf8c3c-27ce-4555-95e6-ee8afa0be4b5-460x276.jpeg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Andrew Dieb/Icon SMI/Icon SMI/Photoshot") (media:description nil "After scoring the winning goal, FC Dallas defender George John is hit in the head with a beer bottle during the game between LA Galaxy and FC Dallas at FC Dallas Stadium. Photograph: Andrew Dieb/Icon SMI/Photoshot")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/blog/2013/apr/17/george-john-fc-dallas-bottle-head")))) ("Sunderland v Everton: squad sheets" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/36337?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Asunderland-everton-squad-sheets%3A1896415&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Sunderland+%28Football%29%2CEverton+%28Football%29%2CPremier+League+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Europa+League%2CPremier+League&c6=&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+01%3A09&c8=1896415&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=Squad+sheets+%28football%29&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Sunderland+v+Everton%3A+squad%26nbsp%3Bsheets&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FSunderland\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p>Paolo Di Canio finally gets to strut his stuff before the Sunderland congregation in his first home match in charge after opening his tenure away at Chelsea and Newcastle. The controversial Italian has already secured a fair portion of adoration from those fans not interested in his politics after last Sunday's emphatic 3-0 win at St James's Park in the Tyneside derby. While his mission is to keep Sunderland up, David Moyes's Everton still cling to faint hopes of qualifying for Champions League football so a draw is unsatisfactory for either team. <strong>Jamie&nbsp;Jackson</strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> Stadium of Light, Saturday 3pm</p><p><strong>Tickets </strong>£27-35 (0871 911 1973)</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>Sunderland 1 Everton 1</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>Phil Dowd</p><p><strong>This season's matches</strong> 21 <strong>Y</strong>60, <strong>R</strong>4, 3.05 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds </strong>Sunderland 5-2 Everton 5-4 Draw 9-4</p><h2><strong>Sunderland</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Westwood, Kilgallon, Bramble, Mangane, Colback, Vaughan, Wickham, Mandron, Laidler</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Bardsley (ankle), Cuéllar (foot), Wickham (knock)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Cattermole (knee, Aug), Fletcher (ankle, Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> Gardner (last of two)</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> WLLDLD</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y53 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Fletcher 11</p><h2><strong>Everton</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Mucha, Heitinga, Naismith, Jelavic, Neville, Vellios, Oviedo, Duffy, Hibbert, Francisco, Hitzlsperger, Barkley</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Hibbert (calf), Osman (thigh)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> None</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DWDWWW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y54 R3</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Fellaini 11</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Sunderland have failed to win any of their past 16 league meetings with Everton, drawing four times and losing the other 12 games</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Tim Howard kept his 100th Premier League clean sheet against Arsenal on Wednesday, becoming the 12th keeper to reach the landmark in this competition</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Stéphane Sessègnon has won more free-kicks (82) this season than any other player</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• In the last three league games between these sides, all seven of Everton's have come after half-time while both of Sunderland's goals have come in the first period</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Sunderland have scored just two headed goals this season, a divisional low, while only Chelsea (14) have scored more than Everton (13) but Sunderland have conceded the joint-fewest headed goals (two) while Everton have conceded the most (14)</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/sunderland\">Sunderland</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/everton\">Everton</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/premierleague\">Premier League</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-se