s matches</strong> 20 <strong>Y</strong>67, <strong>R</strong>2, 3.45 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds </strong>West Brom 6-5 Newcastle 11-5 Draw 5-2</p><h2><strong>West Bromwich Albion</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Daniels, Myhill, Reid, Tamas, Popov, Rosenberg, Fortuné, Long, Allan, Hurst, Roofe, Nabi, Berahino</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Brown (groin, 27 Apr), Odemwingie (knee, 27 Apr), Gera (knee, Aug), Thorne (knee, Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> Mulumbu (second of three)</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LLDWLW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y55 R3</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Lukaku 13</p><h2><strong>Newcastle</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Harper, Simpson, Williamson, Perch, Gosling, Amalfitano, Campbell, Haïdara, Bigirimana, Shola&nbsp;Ameobi, Obertan, Tavernier</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Coloccini (back, 27 Apr), Santon (hamstring, 27 Apr), Tioté (knock, 27 Apr), Vuckic (knee, 19 May), Marveaux (groin, unknown), Krul (shoulder, Aug), R Taylor (knee, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LWLLWL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y63 R2</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Cissé 8</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Albion have won just two of their past 13 league meetings with Newcastle</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Newcastle have drawn just one of their past 23 Premier League games, winning seven times and losing 15</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Three of Albion's last six league goals have come from the penalty spot, while another was an own goal</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Newcastle have been forced to make more clearances (1,396) than any other side in the division</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Albion have been awarded the most yellow cards for time-wasting (seven) in the top flight</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; mar