ors need to consolidate a top-four berth before the exertions of a demanding fixture list take their toll, while former Chelsea reserve manager Brendan Rodgers has to prevent Liverpool's season petering out with a whimper with Everton six points ahead. The improving form of another ex-Anfield favourite, Fernando Torres, adds to the intrigue surrounding this strange reunion. <strong>Andy&nbsp;Hunter</strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> Anfield, Sunday 4pm</p><p><strong>Tickets </strong>Sold out</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>Liverpool 4 Chelsea 1</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>Kevin Friend</p><p><strong>This season's matches</strong> 18 <strong>Y</strong>66, <strong>R</strong>1, 3.72 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds </strong>Liverpool 11-10 Chelsea 5-2 Draw 9-4</p><h2><strong>Liverpool</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Gulacsi, Jones, Assaidi, Downing, Suso, Shelvey, Coady, Yesil, Skrtel, Wisdom, Coates</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> None</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Flanagan (knee, 27 Apr), Borini (shoulder, 5 May), Kelly (knee, 5 May), Sterling (thigh, 12 May), Allen (shoulder, Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DDWLWW</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y44 R2</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Suárez 22</p><h2><strong>Chelsea</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Hilário, Turnbull, Ferreira, Cahill, Cole, Terry, Lampard, Marin, Torres, Moses, Ake, Benayoun</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Cahill (match fitness), Cole (match fitness), Marin (thigh)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Romeu (knee, Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> WWLWWL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y42 R2</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Lampard 12</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Chelsea have won only one of their past six top-flight games at Anfield and failed to score in three of them</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Liverpool have been caught 