ty") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Premier League") (pubDate nil "Fri, 19 Apr 2013 14:53:38 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/qpr-stoke-city-squad-sheets") (dc:creator nil) (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-19T15:04:07Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407524886") (media:keywords nil "QPR, Stoke City, Premier League, Football, Sport") (media:content ((height . "650") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Sport/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366383126963/QPR-v-Stoke-City-001.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Graphic") (media:description nil "Queens Park Rangers v Stoke City: Probable starters in bold, contenders in light. Illustration: Graphic")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/qpr-stoke-city-squad-sheets"))) ("Ferguson relieved to leave 'war zone'" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/6768?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Amanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson%3A1896549&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Manchester+United+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=Jamie+Jackson&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+03%3A49&c8=1896549&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Manchester+United%27s+manager+delighted+to+have+left+West+Ham+%27war+zone%27&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FManchester+United\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• United name same squad for Aston Villa on Monday<br />• 'Rooney was not playing as well as Shinji Kagawa'</p><p>Sir Alex Ferguson is relieved at having left the \"war zone\" of Upton Park with no injuries to his Manchester United players following Wednesday's 2-2 draw with West Ham United.</p><p>After the match Ferguson claimed that West Ham's Andy Carroll should have been sent off for colliding with David de Gea, United's goalkeeper, before half-time. Later in the game Carroll also clashed with Nemanja Vidic.</p><p>United face Aston Villa on Monday evening knowing that victory would secure a 20th title if Manchester City lose at Tottenham Hotspur the day before, and Ferguson is happy that, despite the attritional test posed by West Ham, he can name the same squad.</p><p>\"We have a few bumps and bruises. Vida [Vidic] has a beautiful bruise on his cheekbone,\" the Scot said. \"I think after coming out of that war zone I am pleased there is no one seriously injured.</p><p>\"The team were fantastic in terms of standing up. It's the type of games you get against Sam's [Allardyce] teams. We had to deal with it. A point was deserved and we could have won it in the last 20 minutes, but it's satisfying to come from going behind twice in the game.</p><p>\"I have the same squad for Aston Villa. Hopefully we pick the right team because every game seems more important than the last one. When you get nearer that line that's the way it is. Hopefully we'll pick the right team.\"</p><p>Regarding Carroll's challenge on De Gea, Ferguson added: \"It was a red card, there's no disputing that. I think Sam is the master of talking about being robbed in a game and that masks the actual fact that they should have had 10 men for the [rest of] game. It didn't happen. It's gone and doesn't affect us any more.\"</p><p>Ferguson believes the Football Association's regulations, which ensure there can be no retrospective action for Carroll as the incident was seen by the referee, are muddled. \"To be honest, I don't know where they are now. I've no idea,\" the manager said. \"I don't think there is no clarity now. There's so many things that probably need a bit of clarity.\"</p><p>Wayne Rooney was replaced during the second half at Upton Park to spark further speculation about his future, but Ferguson stated the reason was simply a matter of the England international's form. \"As far as taking him off on Wednesday, it's simply because he wasn't playing as well as Shinji [Kagawa] was,\" he said.</p><p>\"We had to get that goal that mattered and of course there are so many games Wayne Rooney is better than most players. But on the night Shinji was playing so well.</p><p>\"The ironic thing was when we were chasing the goal with 40 minutes left I decided to put Javier Hernández on [for Kagawa]. And Shinji makes the second goal. I'd already made the substitution and given the fourth official the card. And Javier was stood on the touchline when we scored the second goal.</p><p>\"I think if I'd have changed my decision then I think we'd have won the game because Shinji was doing really well. Unfortunately he came off and Javier came on simply because he will get a chance in the game. At that point we wanted to win it and you make decisions like that.\"</p><p>Ferguson has selected Rooney in midfield recently, so will he do so again? \"Difficult to say,\" he said. \"We're picking teams to win and we did that at Stoke [on Sunday]. I'll be doing the same on Monday.\"</p><p>Ferguson is also surprised at reports linking Rooney to a summer move to Paris St-Germain. \"I don't think there is anything in that at all,\" the manager said, before stating he could not discuss any information regarding discussions over preparing a new deal for the former Everton player.</p><p>Rooney, who wants to stay at Old Trafford, will have two years remaining on his contract then.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/manchester-united\">Manchester United</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/jamiejackson\">Jamie Jackson</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aeb9691/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fmanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson&t=Ferguson+relieved+to+leave+%27war+zone%27\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fmanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson&t=Ferguson+relieved+to+leave+%27war+zone%27\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fmanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson&t=Ferguson+relieved+to+leave+%27war+zone%27\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fmanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson&t=Ferguson+relieved+to+leave+%27war+zone%27\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fmanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson&t=Ferguson+relieved+to+leave+%27war+zone%27\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644680020/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aeb9691/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644680020/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aeb9691/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644680020/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aeb9691/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/_rspfMaBGrA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>" "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/_rspfMaBGrA/manchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson" (20849 22892) old 17 nil nil ((title nil "Ferguson relieved to leave 'war zone'") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/_rspfMaBGrA/manchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/6768?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Amanchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson%3A1896549&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Manchester+United+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=Jamie+Jackson&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+03%3A49&c8=1896549&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Manchester+United%27s+manager+delighted+to+have+left+West+Ham+%27war+zone%27&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FManchester+United\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• United name same squad for Aston Villa on Monday<br />• 'Rooney was not playing as well as Shinji Kagawa'</p><p>Sir Alex Ferguson is relieved at having left the \"war zone\" of Upton Park with no injuries to his Manchester United players following Wednesday's 2-2 draw with West Ham United.</p><p>After the match Ferguson claimed that West Ham's Andy Carroll should have been sent off for colliding with David de Gea, United's goalkeeper, before half-time. Later in the game Carroll also clashed with Nemanja Vidic.</p><p>United face Aston Villa on Monday evening knowing that victory would secure a 20th title if Manchester City lose at Tottenham Hotspur the day before, and Ferguson is happy that, despite the attritional test posed by West Ham, he can name the same squad.</p><p>\"We have a few bumps and bruises. Vida [Vidic] has a beautiful bruise on his cheekbone,\" the Scot said. \"I think after coming out of that war zone I am pleased there is no one seriously injured.</p><p>\"The team were fantastic in terms of standing up. It's the type of games you get against Sam's [Allardyce] teams. We had to deal with it. A point was deserved and we could have won it in the last 20 minutes, but it's satisfying to come from going behind twice in the game.</p><p>\"I have the same squad for Aston Villa. Hopefully we pick the right team because every game seems more important than the last one. When you get nearer that line that's the way it is. Hopefully we'll pick the right team.\"</p><p>Regarding Carroll's challenge on De Gea, Ferguson added: \"It was a red card, there's no disputing that. I think Sam is the master of talking about being robbed in a game and that masks the actual fact that they should have had 10 men for the [rest of] game. It didn't happen. It's gone and doesn't affect us any more.\"</p><p>Ferguson believes the Football Association's regulations, which ensure there can be no retrospective action for Carroll as the incident was seen by the referee, are muddled. \"To be honest, I don't know where they are now. I've no idea,\" the manager said. \"I don't think there is no clarity now. There's so many things that probably need a bit of clarity.\"</p><p>Wayne Rooney was replaced during the second half at Upton Park to spark further speculation about his future, but Ferguson stated the reason was simply a matter of the England international's form. \"As far as taking him off on Wednesday, it's simply because he wasn't playing as well as Shinji [Kagawa] was,\" he said.</p><p>\"We had to get that goal that mattered and of course there are so many games Wayne Rooney is better than most players. But on the night Shinji was playing so well.</p><p>\"The ironic thing was when we were chasing the goal with 40 minutes left I decided to put Javier Hernández on [for Kagawa]. And Shinji makes the second goal. I'd already made the substitution and given the fourth official the card. And Javier was stood on the touchline when we scored the second goal.</p><p>\"I think if I'd have changed my decision then I think we'd have won the game because Shinji was doing really well. Unfortunately he came off and Javier came on simply because he will get a chance in the game. At that point we wanted to win it and you make decisions like that.\"</p><p>Ferguson has selected Rooney in midfield recently, so will he do so again? \"Difficult to say,\" he said. \"We're picking teams to win and we did that at Stoke [on Sunday]. I'll be doing the same on Monday.\"</p><p>Ferguson is also surprised at reports linking Rooney to a summer move to Paris St-Germain. \"I don't think there is anything in that at all,\" the manager said, before stating he could not discuss any information regarding discussions over preparing a new deal for the former Everton player.</p><p>Rooney, who wants to stay at Old Trafford, will have two years remaining on his contract then.</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/manchester-united\">Manchester United</a></li></ul></div><div class=\"author\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/profile/jamiejackson\">Jamie Jackson</a></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aeb9691/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><tabl