MaBGrA\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Guardian") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Manchester United") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "Sport") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (pubDate nil "Fri, 19 Apr 2013 14:49:16 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/manchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson") (dc:creator nil "Jamie Jackson") (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-19T14:49:16Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407524434") (media:keywords nil "Manchester United, Football, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366382595154/ferguson--003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media/Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media") (media:description nil "Manchester United's manager Sir Alex Ferguson checks his watch in the 2-2 draw at West Ham. Photograph: Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366382601816/ferguson--008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media/Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media") (media:description nil "Manchester United's manager Sir Alex Ferguson gestures with his watch in the 2-2 draw at West Ham. Photograph: Xinhua /Landov / Barcroft Media")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/manchester-united-sir-alex-ferguson"))) ("Swansea City v Sunderland: squad sheets" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/71722?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Aswansea-city-sunderland-squad-sheets%3A1896660&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Swansea+City+%28football+club%29%2CSunderland+%28Football%29%2CPremier+League+%28Football%29%2CFootball%2CSport&c5=Premier+League&c6=&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+05%3A14&c8=1896660&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=Squad+sheets+%28football%29&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Swansea+City+v+Sunderland%3A+squad%26nbsp%3Bsheets&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FSwansea+City\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p>Southampton have found form at just the right time this season, with a five-match unbeaten run that could prove crucial in their quest to survive in the top flight, while Swansea appear to have suffered a Carling Cup hangover since winning the trophy in February. With Europa League qualification already secured, Michael Laudrup's main concern could be motivating his players for the last few games, although the end of season lull does provide him with a chance to ease Neil Taylor back into the side after a long absence with a broken ankle. <strong>Rich&nbsp;Flower</strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> Liberty Stadium, Saturday 3pm</p><p><strong>Tickets </strong>Sold out</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>n/a</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>Mark Halsey</p><p><strong>This season's matches</strong> 15 <strong>Y</strong>37, <strong>R</strong>2, 2.60 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds </strong>Swansea 7-5 Southampton 2-1 Draw 5-2</p><h2><strong>Swansea</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Tremmel, Bartley, Taylor, Tate, Hernández, Lamah, Tiendalli, Ki, Monk, Shechter, Situ, Agustien, Lucas</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Taylor (ankle)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> None</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DLLLWL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y52 R2</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Michu 17</p><h2><strong>Southampton</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> K Davis, Gazzaniga, Hooiveld, Rodriguez, Forren, Ward-Prowse, Shaw, Mayuka, Richardson, Puncheon</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> K&nbsp;Davis (leg), Du&nbsp;Prado (illness), Fonte (personal reasons)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Chaplow (ankle, Aug)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DWWWDL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y38 R0</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Lambert 14</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Michu has contributed a higher ratio of his team's goals (39%) than any other player in the Premier League</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Southampton's last win at Sweansea in any competition came back in January 1962 </strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Swansea have scored 43 league goals so far this season, only one short of equaling their tally for the whole of 2011-12</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Southampton have not lost in five league games, only Everton (six) are currently on a longer unbeaten run</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Wayne Routledge has committed more fouls without being booked (34) than any other player in the top flight</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/swansea\">Swansea City</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/sunderland\">Sunderland</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/premierleague\">Premier League</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aeca963/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"