 (thigh)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Surman (knee, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LDLDDL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y52 R1</p><p><strong>Leading scorers</strong> Holt, Snodgrass 5</p><h2><strong>Reading</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Andersen, Taylor, Pearce, Leigertwood, Hunt, Harte, Blackman, Carriço, Robson-Kanu, Shorey, Henley</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Robson-Kanu (knee)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Akpan (ankle, 28 Apr), Federici (ankle, 28 Apr), Roberts (hip, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DLLLLL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y40 R1</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Le&nbsp;Fondre 10</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Norwich have won just one of their past seven league meetings with Reading – losing on four occasions</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Reading players have made more goalline clearances (11) than any other side in the top flight this season</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Michael Turner has scored as many goals (two) in his past two Premier League games as he did in his previous 88</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Alex McCarthy made 10 saves in Reading's last match (against Liverpool), only Jussi Jaaskelainen has made more in a single game in 2012-13 (11 for West Ham against Tottenham)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Norwich are the only side yet to score from outside the box in open play this season</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/norwichcity\">Norwich City</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/reading\">Reading</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/premierleague\">Premier League</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Lim