a side that know they are doomed to relegation. John Ruddy could feature in the host's squad formthe first time since suffering a thigh injury against former club Everton in November. <strong>Rich&nbsp;Flower</strong></p><p><strong>Venue</strong> Carrow Road, Saturday 3pm</p><p><strong>Tickets </strong>£10-45 (0844 826 1902)</p><p><strong>Last season </strong>n/a</p><p><strong>Referee </strong>Mike Dean</p><p><strong>This season's matches</strong> 23 <strong>Y</strong>88, <strong>R</strong>3, 3.96 cards per game</p><p><strong>Odds </strong>Norwich 3-4 Reading 4-1 Draw 11-4</p><h2><strong>Norwich</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Camp, Ruddy, Steer, Howson, Jackson, Smith, Kamara, E&nbsp;Bennett, Fox, Garrido, Becchio, Tierney, R&nbsp;Bennett</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Ruddy (thigh)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Surman (knee, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> LDLDDL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y52 R1</p><p><strong>Leading scorers</strong> Holt, Snodgrass 5</p><h2><strong>Reading</strong></h2><p><strong>Subs from</strong> Andersen, Taylor, Pearce, Leigertwood, Hunt, Harte, Blackman, Carriço, Robson-Kanu, Shorey, Henley</p><p><strong>Doubtful</strong> Robson-Kanu (knee)</p><p><strong>Injured</strong> Akpan (ankle, 28 Apr), Federici (ankle, 28 Apr), Roberts (hip, unknown)</p><p><strong>Suspended</strong> None</p><p><strong>Form guide</strong> DLLLLL</p><p><strong>Disciplinary record</strong> Y40 R1</p><p><strong>Leading scorer</strong> Le&nbsp;Fondre 10</p><h2><strong>Match pointers</strong></h2><p><strong>• Norwich have won just one of their past seven league meetings with Reading – losing on four occasions</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Reading players have made more goalline clearances (11) than any other side in the top flight this season</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Michael Turner has scored as many goals (two) in his past two Premier League games as he did in his previous 88</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Alex McCarthy made 10 saves in Reading's last match (against Liverpool), only Jussi Jaaskelainen has made more in a single game in 2012-13 (11 for West Ham against Tottenham)</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>• Norwich are the only side yet to score from outside the box in open play this season</strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/norwichcity\">Norwich City</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/reading\">Reading</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/premierleague\">Premier League</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aec2443/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fnorwich-city-reading-squad-sheets&t=Norwich+City+v+Reading%3A+squad%C2%A0sheets\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fnorwich-city-reading-squad-sheets&t=Norwich+City+v+Reading%3A+squad%C2%A0sheets\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fnorwich-city-rea