nil "Ups and downs: What they need in the Football League divisions") (link nil "http://feeds.guardian.co.uk/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~3/wTQnxFTnNx4/football-league-ups-and-downs") (description nil "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/96056?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Afootball-league-ups-and-downs%3A1896670&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Football+League%2CBlue+Square+Premier%2CDoncaster+%28Football+club%29%2CFootball%2CAldershot+Town+%28Football%29%2CSport&c5=Not+commercially+useful&c6=Guardian+Sport+staff&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+05%3A28&c8=1896670&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+all+the+Football+League+divisions&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FFootball+League\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• Doncaster need a win for Championship football<br />• Aldershot on the brink of demotion to Conference<br /><br /></p><h2><strong>Championship </strong></h2><p><strong>Hull City</strong> will be promoted if Watford fail to take as many points from their match against Blackburn as Steve Bruce's team achieve against Bristol City on Friday night.</p><p></p><h2><strong>League One</strong></h2><p><strong>Doncaster Rovers</strong> will return to the Championship with a win in their penultimate game against Notts County. Brian Flynn's side sit three points above Brentford with two games remaining. Only victory at MK Dons could prolong <strong>Scunthorpe's</strong> stay in League One. Survival is out of their hands, however, as a win for Colchester and Oldham would relegate the Iron.</p><p></p><h2><strong>League Two</strong></h2><p>A win over Northampton in their penultimate game would all but secure <strong>Port Vale's</strong> return to League One. Defeat to Dagenham & Redbridge would see <strong>Aldershot</strong> drop out of the Football League. <strong>Barnet</strong> could also be relegated if they lose to Wycombe and the three sides above them win.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Blue Square Bet Premier</strong></h2><p><strong>Mansfield</strong> will be promoted if they beat Wrexham. If they lose, <strong>Kidderminster</strong> will be promoted with a win against Stockport. Stockport need a win to have a chance of avoiding relegation. <strong>Dan Matthews </strong></p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/football-league\">Football League</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/bluesquarepremier\">Blue Square Premier</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/doncaster\">Doncaster Rovers</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/aldershottownfootball\">Aldershot Town</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aec2e52/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Ffootball-league-ups-and-downs&t=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+the+Football+League+divisions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Ffootball-league-ups-and-downs&t=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+the+Football+League+divisions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Ffootball-league-ups-and-downs&t=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+the+Football+League+divisions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Ffootball-league-ups-and-downs&t=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+the+Football+League+divisions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Ffootball-league-ups-and-downs&t=Ups+and+downs%3A+What+they+need+in+the+Football+League+divisions\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png\" border=\"0\" /></a></td></tr></table></div><br/><br/><a href=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644760670/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aec2e52/a2.htm\"><img src=\"http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644760670/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aec2e52/a2.img\" border=\"0\"/></a><img width=\"1\" height=\"1\" src=\"http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644760670/u/49/f/639039/c/34708/s/2aec2e52/a2t.img\" border=\"0\"/><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/theguardian/football/rss/~4/wTQnxFTnNx4\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/publication")) "The Guardian") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Aldershot Town") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football League") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Football") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/sport")) "Sport") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/tone")) "News") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Doncaster Rovers") (category ((domain . "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football")) "Blue Square Premier") (pubDate nil "Fri, 19 Apr 2013 16:28:14 GMT") (guid ((isPermaLink . "false")) "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/football-league-ups-and-downs") (dc:creator nil) (dc:subject nil "Football") (dc:date nil "2013-04-19T16:30:21Z") (dc:type nil "Article") (dc:identifier nil "407532413") (media:keywords nil "Football League, Blue Square Premier, Doncaster Rovers, Football, Aldershot Town, Sport") (media:content ((height . "84") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "140") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366388555669/-Doncaster-Rovers-003.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Paul Burrows/Action Images") (media:description nil "Doncaster's Billy Paynter, right, celebrates with team-mates after scoring his and the team's second goal in last week's 2–1 win at Crewe. Photograph: Paul Burrows/Action Images")) (media:content ((height . "276") (lang . " ") (type . "image/jpeg") (width . "460") (url . "http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Football/Pix/pictures/2013/4/19/1366388562168/-Doncaster-Rovers-008.jpg")) (media:credit ((scheme . "urn:ebu")) "Paul Burrows/Action Images") (media:description nil "Doncaster's Billy Paynter, right, celebrates with team-mates after scoring his and the team's second goal in last week's 2–1 win at Crewe. Photograph: Paul Burrows/Action Images")) (feedburner:origLink nil "http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/2013/apr/19/football-league-ups-and-downs"))) ("Green resigns as Rangers CEO" "<div class=\"track\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://hits.guardian.co.uk/b/ss/guardiangu-feeds/1/H.25.4/4637?ns=guardian&pageName=Article%3Acharles-green-resigns-rangers-chief-executive%3A1896667&ch=Football&c3=Guardian&c4=Rangers+%28Football+club%29%2CFootball%2CSport%2CScottish+Division+Three&c5=Not+commercially+useful%2CScottish+Football&c6=Press+Association&c7=2013%2F04%2F19+05%3A25&c8=1896667&c9=Article&c10=News&c13=&c19=GUK&c47=UK&c64=UK&c65=Charles+Green+resigns+as+Rangers+chief+executive+as+club+investigates&c66=Sport&c72=&c73=&c74=&c75=&h2=GU%2FSport%2FFootball%2FRangers\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" /></div><p class=\"standfirst\">• Development follows claims from former owner Craig Whyte<br />• Green maintains he has done nothing wrong</p><p>Charles Green has stepped down from his position as chief executive at Rangers with immediate effect, the Third Division club have told the Stock Exchange.</p><p>The Rangers board announced last week that they will commission an independent investigation into Green's and Imran Ahmad's management of the club and recent allegations in the media.</p><p>The investigation was launched after the club's directors – including the former manager Walter Smith – met at Murray Park last weekend.</p><p>The summit followed claims made by the former owner Craig Whyte of his involvement with Green and the commercial director Ahmad when their consortium completed the purchase of Rangers' business and assets last summer.</p><p>Green – who recently apologised after being charged by the Scottish Football Association for allegedly using \"racist and offensive language\" – rejected the allegations by Whyte, who was in charge when the club plunged into administration and subsequently liquidation. It is understood that Green feels the decision to step down as chief executive is in the best interests of the club, following recent adverse publicity, but that he remains adamant he has done nothing wrong. He is the club's largest single shareholder.</p><p>The Rangers manager, Ally McCoist, speaking at his pre-match press conference on Friday, ahead of Saturday's visit of Peterhead, was asked when he was last in contact with Green.</p><p>McCoist said: \"I haven't spoken to him verbally since last weekend but I've been in contact via emails and a couple of texts. As far as I know, he's in France having a well-earned break.</p><p>\"I don't have any doubt we will meet up when he comes back. We've got a lot to discuss in taking the club forward in terms of players and pre-season training and all that stuff.\"</p><div class=\"related\" style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/rangers\">Rangers</a></li><li><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/football/scottish-division-three\">Scottish Division Three</a></li></ul></div><br/><div class=\"terms\"><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk\">guardian.co.uk</a> &copy; 2013 Guardian News and Media Limited or its affiliated companies. All rights reserved. | Use of this content is subject to our <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/terms-of-service\">Terms & Conditions</a> | <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/feeds\">More Feeds</a></div><p style=\"clear:both\" /><img width='1' height='1' src='http://guardian.co.uk.feedsportal.com/c/34708/f/639039/s/2aec9901/mf.gif' border='0'/><div class='mf-viral'><table border='0'><tr><td valign='middle'><a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fcharles-green-resigns-rangers-chief-executive&t=Green+resigns+as+Rangers+CEO\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fcharles-green-resigns-rangers-chief-executive&t=Green+resigns+as+Rangers+CEO\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co.uk%2Ffootball%2F2013%2Fapr%2F19%2Fcharles-green-resigns-rangers-chief-executive&t=Green+resigns+as+Rangers+CEO\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png\" border=\"0\" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.guardian.co